      • StartDate

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key StartDate

      • EndDate

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key EndDate
        The latest date that may be selected; all later dates will be disabled.

      • StartView

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key StartView
        The view that the datepicker should show when it is opened. Accepts values of 0 or 'month' for month view (the default), 1 or 'year' for the 12-month overview, and 2 or 'decade' for the 10-year overview. Useful for date-of-birth datepickers.

      • ShowTodayButton

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key ShowTodayButton
        If true, displays a "Today" button at the bottom of the datepicker to select the current date. If true, the "Today" button will only move the current date into view;

      • KeyboardNavigation

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key KeyboardNavigation
        Whether or not to allow date navigation by arrow keys.

      • Language

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key Language
        The two-letter code of the language to use for month and day names. These will also be used as the input's value (and subsequently sent to the server in the case of form submissions). Currently ships with English ('en'), German ('de'), Brazilian ('br'), and Spanish ('es') translations, but others can be added (see I18N below). If an unknown language code is given, English will be used.

      • Format

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key Format
        The date format, combination of d, dd, m, mm, M, MM, yy, yyyy.

      • WeekStart

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key WeekStart

      • HighlightToday

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key HighlightToday
        If true, highlights the current date.

      • AutoClose

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key AutoClose
        Whether or not to close the datepicker immediately when a date is selected.

      • ForceParse

        public static final DateTextFieldConfig.Key ForceParse
        Whether or not to force parsing of the input value when the picker is closed. That is, when an invalid date is left in the input field by the user, the picker will forcibly parse that value, and set the input's value to the new, valid date, conforming to the given format.
